news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Rajaji Nagar Colony revamp to be delayed due to bid issue
news.para: Though Smart City Thiruvananthapuram Ltd (SCTL), the project’s implementing agency, had invited e-tenders, only two took part in the bid. Of the two, one company opted out as it could not meet the qualification criteria.

news.title: Noida residents seek last-mile link from metro stations
news.para: “We have written to the Noida Authority CEO to propose routes for the operation of e-buses till they plan a dedicated and mandatory public transport system for the city,” said PS Jain, president of CONRWA.

news.title: Labour shortage in Vijayawada hits construction sector
news.para: Election campaigns gained pace across the state after Election Commission of India (ECI) declared the election schedule. All major political parties are conducting public meetings, political rallies and road shows to attract the voters.

news.title: UP-RERA directs complainants to include names of co-allottees
news.para: UP-RERA has observed that joint allotment of houses or shops is a common practice. Their interests do not necessarily co-inside always and disputes between such co-allotees or co-owners do sometimes arise.

news.title: West Bengal CM asks officials to take stern action against illegal buildings
news.para: Since Thursday, the CM is nursing an injury on her forehead that required four stitches. Monday was her first public appearance since the fall at home.

news.title: Rules flouted, low-quality materials used in collapsed building: Kolkata civic body official
news.para: Builders of the collapsed multi-storey building in Kolkata's Garden Reach area had flouted several rules of the Kolkata Municipal Corporation (KMC) to erect a new building which led to the disaster, a senior official said on Monday.

news.title: Only one out of every five homes in Bengaluru has rainwater harvesting
news.para: While there are 17,591 apartments with less than 20 houses implementing RWH, there are 3,034 apartments with over 20 households in an apartment complex that have adopted the practice.

news.title: Kishore Biyani offers Rs 476 crore as one-time settlement for BMMCPL's debt
news.para: The Biyani offer comes just days after creditors had approved a Rs 475-crore bid from Runwal Group for the asset through an auction process, multiple people familiar with the development said.

news.title: Delhi HC asks MCD on what basis Signature View Apartments has been declared dangerous
news.para: Delhi HC questions MCD on declaring Signature View Apartments dangerous. Centre's stance needed. Attri opposes demolition sans due process. Stay extended, hearing set for April 22. Union of India to assess repair feasibility.

news.title: Hyderabad: ED attaches four floors of Hotel One Continent in PMLA case
news.para: ED had initiated investigation on the basis of an FIR lodged by Punjab & Maharashtra Co-operative Bank (PMC) against Joy Thomas, Waryam Singh (directors of PMC Bank), Rakesh Kumar Wadhawan, Sarang Wadhawan and unknown other persons.

news.title: Noida authority proposes to recover unused Unitech land, adjust it against dues
news.para: Supreme Court weighs options for Unitech's housing projects in Noida. Noida Authority seeks unused land return for dues adjustment. Unitech plans construction post approvals, facing hurdles in project clearances and due payments.

news.title: UP-RERA asks Ghaziabad development body why flat not handed after two orders
news.para: Sarla Devi of Sonipat was supposed to get a flat in Madhuban Bapudham under the govt scheme. In 2021, she filed a case with the real estate regulator seeking possession of the flat.

news.title: Asking prices for homes in UK rise by most in 10 months: Survey
news.para: Property website Rightmove said asking prices for residential properties rose by 1.5% in the four weeks to March 9, the strongest four-week increase in 10 months, although they remained nearly 5,000 pounds ($6,400) below their May 2023 peak.

news.title: Sweden's SBB offers to buy back more debt
news.para: Loss-making SBB, at the epicentre of a Swedish property crash, late last year spent 403.8 million euros ($440 million) to buy back debt at a small discount to the nominal value.

news.title: Property investment in China dips 9% year-on-year in Jan-Feb 2024
news.para: Property investment in China fell 9.0% year-on-year in the first two months of 2024, compared with a 24.0% fall in December 2023, National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data showed.

news.title: Mumbai: Survey for Dharavi redevelopment project begins from Kamla Raman Nagar
news.para: SVR Srinivas, CEO of the Dharavi Redevelopment Project, said that the project is a very important one, and today we have begun the survey.

news.title: Chandigarh administration approves interim budget worth Rs 300 crore for civic body
news.para: Chandigarh's Municipal Corporation to spend Rs 100 crore monthly for 3 months on liabilities. UT approved Rs 300 crore interim budget. Decision awaited on March 6 meeting. MC submits 2022-2025 budget estimates.

news.title: Bengaluru: Road connectivity at Nadaprabhu Kempegowda layout comes with land loss for some
news.para: The BDA would treat the applicants as being entitled to priority allotment and allot each of them a site measuring 30x40 sq ft in the Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout.

news.title: Residents of Lucknow to receive combined water and house tax from FY25
news.para: Corporator Laeeq Agha, a member of the EC, praised the decision, stating, “This initiative not only simplifies the tax collection process, but also encourages proactive participation from residents in contributing towards the development of our city.”

news.title: Fractional ownership of real estate assets through SM REITs
news.para: Fractional ownership of real estate can offer diversification, accessibility to high-value properties, and potential investment returns, but it also comes with risks and complexities (such as low rental yield during COVID-19).
